There's a whole idea from
Joseph Chilton Pearce,

00:23:39.730 --> 00:23:43.720 align:middle line:84%
that ultimately there's a
human need for transcendence.

00:23:43.720 --> 00:23:45.390 align:middle line:90%
Or initiatory experience.

00:23:45.390 --> 00:23:48.110 align:middle line:84%
Like something that--
that's why people

00:23:48.110 --> 00:23:51.440 align:middle line:84%
seek out ayahuaska and
shamanic experience and so on.

00:23:51.440 --> 00:23:53.400 align:middle line:84%
Is that a possible
future direction?

00:23:53.400 --> 00:23:54.930 align:middle line:84%
Do you find that
through meditation?

00:23:54.930 --> 00:23:56.360 align:middle line:90%
You encounter those types of--

00:23:56.360 --> 00:23:57.280 align:middle line:90%
I got no choice, have I?

00:23:57.280 --> 00:23:58.679 align:middle line:84%
Cause I got a big--
the whole drug problem

00:23:58.679 --> 00:24:00.530 align:middle line:90%
and abstinence based recovery.

00:24:00.530 --> 00:24:02.590 align:middle line:84%
So for me-- but I agree
that you're right.

00:24:02.590 --> 00:24:04.920 align:middle line:84%
I think a certain
percentage of the population

00:24:04.920 --> 00:24:07.630 align:middle line:84%
probably needs
transcendent experiences.

00:24:07.630 --> 00:24:09.480 align:middle line:84%
I don't know how
early societies were

00:24:09.480 --> 00:24:11.000 align:middle line:90%
formalized-- tribal societies.

00:24:11.000 --> 00:24:12.490 align:middle line:84%
But I don't imagine
everyone in the village

00:24:12.490 --> 00:24:14.680 align:middle line:84%
was a witch doctor,
necking bunches of plants

00:24:14.680 --> 00:24:15.620 align:middle line:90%
and having crazy visions.

00:24:15.620 --> 00:24:17.390 align:middle line:84%
Cause who's gonna
[BLEEP] cut the crops

00:24:17.390 --> 00:24:19.290 align:middle line:84%
and look after all the
cooking and everything?

00:24:19.290 --> 00:24:22.120 align:middle line:84%
But some people have got to
have transcendent experiences,

00:24:22.120 --> 00:24:23.560 align:middle line:84%
so they can report
back like, ah, you

00:24:23.560 --> 00:24:25.000 align:middle line:90%
think that this is all real.

00:24:25.000 --> 00:24:26.200 align:middle line:90%
Don't worry, it's not.

00:24:26.200 --> 00:24:27.120 align:middle line:90%
Relax.

00:24:27.120 --> 00:24:28.040 align:middle line:90%
You make a pot.

00:24:28.040 --> 00:24:28.780 align:middle line:90%
You do some cooking.

00:24:28.780 --> 00:24:29.940 align:middle line:90%
All right, cool.

00:24:29.940 --> 00:24:32.610 align:middle line:84%
Everyone can't be the shaman,
otherwise, who's gonna wash up?

00:24:32.610 --> 00:24:36.370 align:middle line:84%
But also, what are
transcendent experiences?

00:24:36.370 --> 00:24:38.060 align:middle line:84%
To me-- and I'm in
the same boat as you,

00:24:38.060 --> 00:24:40.805 align:middle line:84%
having been off drugs and
alcohol for a long time.

00:24:40.805 --> 00:24:41.755 align:middle line:90%
It's hard, isn't it?

00:24:41.755 --> 00:24:43.370 align:middle line:90%
Oh, yeah, really hard.

00:24:43.370 --> 00:24:45.420 align:middle line:90%
But I've been alive already.

00:24:45.420 --> 00:24:48.440 align:middle line:84%
So one of the things
I feel, for me,

00:24:48.440 --> 00:24:50.820 align:middle line:84%
is transcendence comes
through connection.

00:24:50.820 --> 00:24:51.920 align:middle line:90%
It's really simple.

00:24:51.920 --> 00:24:53.460 align:middle line:84%
It's like, so much
of my life I was

00:24:53.460 --> 00:24:54.740 align:middle line:90%
so afraid to connect to this.

00:24:54.740 --> 00:24:55.490 align:middle line:90%
To this body.

00:24:55.490 --> 00:24:56.600 align:middle line:90%
To this being.

00:24:56.600 --> 00:24:57.390 align:middle line:90%
And to other people.

00:24:57.390 --> 00:24:59.810 align:middle line:84%
Because my heart was
just too vulnerable.

00:24:59.810 --> 00:25:02.320 align:middle line:84%
And now, I feel
like, OK, connection,

00:25:02.320 --> 00:25:03.320 align:middle line:90%
that's where we transcend.

00:25:03.320 --> 00:25:05.670 align:middle line:84%
It's when we actually look
at someone, touch someone.

00:25:05.670 --> 00:25:07.530 align:middle line:90%
They're real, they're physical.

00:25:07.530 --> 00:25:09.266 align:middle line:84%
They're connected to us.
You know?

00:25:09.266 --> 00:25:10.740 align:middle line:90%
Was that some of it then?

00:25:10.740 --> 00:25:12.492 align:middle line:90%
I think so.

00:25:12.492 --> 00:25:14.250 align:middle line:90%
It was.

00:25:14.250 --> 00:25:16.050 align:middle line:90%
That was nice.

00:25:16.050 --> 00:25:17.270 align:middle line:84%
Makes me want to
cry a little bit.

00:25:17.270 --> 00:25:18.260 align:middle line:90%
Oh, I see.

00:25:18.260 --> 00:25:20.370 align:middle line:84%
So the self is an
artificial construct,

00:25:20.370 --> 00:25:21.870 align:middle line:84%
and we can begin
to diminish this

00:25:21.870 --> 00:25:24.391 align:middle line:84%
by valuing other people and
other people's needs as much

00:25:24.391 --> 00:25:25.890 align:middle line:84%
as our own.
It's in the Bible anyway.

00:25:25.890 --> 00:25:26.160 align:middle line:90%
Love thy neighbor.

00:25:26.160 --> 00:25:27.326 align:middle line:84%
Which we knew when
we were tribal,

00:25:27.326 --> 00:25:29.520 align:middle line:84%
because we didn't even have such
a sense of individual I-self.

00:25:29.520 --> 00:25:31.120 align:middle line:84%
We had more of a
sense of a group self.

00:25:31.120 --> 00:25:33.280 align:middle line:84%
We're a bunch of ants, all
scurrying about helping.

00:25:33.280 --> 00:25:34.680 align:middle line:84%
Well, I heard a story
about these people

00:25:34.680 --> 00:25:36.079 align:middle line:84%
who were making a film
about-- documentary

00:25:36.079 --> 00:25:37.120 align:middle line:90%
about Australian Aboriginals.

00:25:37.120 --> 00:25:38.175 align:middle line:84%
But they showed them a
bunch of documentaries,

00:25:38.175 --> 00:25:39.341 align:middle line:84%
they asked them,
how do they really

00:25:39.341 --> 00:25:42.190 align:middle line:90%
want to be shown in the film?

00:25:42.190 --> 00:25:44.140 align:middle line:84%
They said they didn't want
there to be any closeups.

00:25:44.140 --> 00:25:46.850 align:middle line:84%
They wanted the whole tribe
to be visible in every frame.

00:25:46.850 --> 00:25:47.836 align:middle line:90%
That's beautiful.

00:25:47.836 --> 00:25:48.726 align:middle line:90%
That's beautiful.

00:25:48.726 --> 00:25:50.025 align:middle line:84%
Difficult challenge
for the filmmaker,

00:25:50.025 --> 00:25:53.230 align:middle line:84%
as the closeup is a necessary
component of storytelling.

00:25:53.230 --> 00:25:54.278 align:middle line:90%
Well, maybe.

00:25:54.278 --> 00:25:55.532 align:middle line:90%
Maybe old storytelling.

00:25:55.532 --> 00:25:57.627 align:middle line:84%
Maybe that's the old way of
telling a story, you know?

00:25:57.627 --> 00:25:59.060 align:middle line:84%
Ah, we've got to do
some ch-ch-ch-changes,

00:25:59.060 --> 00:26:00.886 align:middle line:90%
as Ziggy predicted.

00:26:00.886 --> 00:26:01.660 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:26:01.660 --> 00:26:04.060 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, so how do you guys see
that culture could change over

00:26:04.060 --> 00:26:07.300 align:middle line:84%
the next period to kind of
reflect this new realization

00:26:07.300 --> 00:26:09.200 align:middle line:90%
or understanding.

00:26:09.200 --> 00:26:10.200 align:middle line:90%
Have I got a say?

